.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-1-13::.
6 different games are played: scrabble, monopoly, billiard, bridge, domino, mah-jongg
The people use 6 different means of transport: car, motorbike, roller, scooter, tram, trike
1. the person playing bridge is the person driving the roller##1
2. the person playing scrabble is on the left of the person playing mah-jongg##1
3. the person driving the roller is on the left of the person playing scrabble##1
4. the person playing scrabble is the person driving the motorbike##1
5. the person playing monopoly is on the right of the person driving the car##1
6. the person driving the scooter is on the right of the person playing monopoly##1
7. the person playing billiard is on the left of the person driving the tram##1
8. the person driving the car is on the far left##1
9. the person playing mah-jongg is the person driving the trike##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |   1   |     2     |       3        |     4     |     5     |   6    |
| Game         | billiard | monopoly | domino | bridge | scrabble    | mah-jongg |
| Transport   | car   | tram      | scooter        | roller    | motorbike | trike  |

